  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Language Instructor (Extracurriculum)",
  "description": "<h3>Job Description</h3><p>We are seeking passionate and dedicated <strong>Language Instructors (Extracurricular)</strong> to join <strong>Wonderlingo</strong>, a bilingual education centre providing English language enrichment programmes for students aged 1–18 from both local and international school backgrounds.</p><p>The role focuses on delivering high-quality <strong>English enrichment and language development programmes</strong> that support students’ communication skills, academic readiness, and confidence in English, complementing their learning in international school environments.</p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p><p>Teach <strong>1-to-1 and small-group English enrichment classes</strong> using Wonderlingo’s curriculum and teaching materials</p><p>Deliver engaging lessons that develop students’ <strong>reading, writing, speaking, listening, and academic language skills</strong> in an enrichment setting</p><p>Adapt lesson content to meet the needs of students from diverse linguistic and cultural backgrounds</p><p>Support curriculum development, lesson planning, and worksheet editing when required</p><p>Provide constructive and timely feedback to students and parents on learning progress</p><p>Maintain a professional, positive, and engaging learning environment aligned with Wonderlingo’s teaching philosophy</p><p>Participate in training sessions and contribute to educational and curriculum-related projects within the centre<br /><br /><strong>Job Requirements</strong></p><p>Degree in a language-related, humanities, or social sciences discipline</p><p>Recognised English language teaching qualifications (e.g. CELTA, DELTA, TEFL or equivalent)</p><p>Experience teaching English as a second or foreign language</p><p>Experience teaching children and/or adolescents in an enrichment or language centre setting is preferred</p><p>Strong communication and classroom management skills</p><p>Ability to work effectively in a bilingual and multicultural education environment</p><p>Passion for language education and working with learners across different age groups</p>",
